<div class="html-table_show  mfp-hide " id="table_body_display_applsci-14-11836-t001">
  

      <div class="html-caption"><b>Table 1.</b>
    Cases of cyber infringement incidents related to ICS and OT.</div>
      <table >
        <thead  ><tr  ><th align='center' valign='middle' style='border-top:solid thin;border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Victim</th><th align='center' valign='middle' style='border-top:solid thin;border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Nation</th><th align='center' valign='middle' style='border-top:solid thin;border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Year</th><th align='center' valign='middle' style='border-top:solid thin;border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Attack Method</th></tr></thead><tbody  ><tr  ><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Colonial Pipeline</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >USA</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >2021</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Ransomware (Darkside)</td></tr><tr  ><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Sol Oriens</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >USA</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >2021</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Ransomware (REvil)</td></tr><tr  ><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >JBS Foods</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >USA</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >2021</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Ransomware (REvil)</td></tr><tr  ><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Honda</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Japan</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >2020</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Ransomware (EKANS)</td></tr><tr  ><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Norsk Hydro</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Norway</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >2019</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Ransomware (LockerGoga)</td></tr><tr  ><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Lake City</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >USA</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >2019</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Ransomware (Ryuk)</td></tr><tr  ><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Wood Ranch Medical</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >USA</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >2019</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Ransomware</td></tr><tr  ><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Saudi Arabia petrochemical plant</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Saudi</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >2017</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >APT Attack</td></tr><tr  ><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Ukrainian region power supply company</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Ukraine</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >2015/2016</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >APT Attack (Black Energy)</td></tr><tr  ><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Iran Bucer Nuclear Power Plant</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Iran</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >2010</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >APT Attack (Stuxnet)</td></tr></tbody>
      </table>



</div>
<div class="html-table-wrap"
  id="applsci-14-11836-t002"
  
  data-position="float"
>
  <div class="html-table_wrap_td">
    <div class="html-tablepopup html-tablepopup-link" data-counterslinkmanual = "https://www.mdpi.com/2076-3417/14/24/11836/display"
  href='#table_body_display_applsci-14-11836-t002'>
        <img data-lsrc="https://pub.mdpi-res.com/img/table.png" />
       <a class="html-expand html-tablepopup" data-counterslinkmanual = "https://www.mdpi.com/2076-3417/14/24/11836/display"
  href="#table_body_display_applsci-14-11836-t002"></a>
    </div>

  </div>
  <div class="html-table_wrap_discription">
    <b>Table 2.</b>
    Functions and usage according to the distinction between SIEM and ESM.
  </div>
</div>
<div class="html-table_show  mfp-hide " id="table_body_display_applsci-14-11836-t002">
  

      <div class="html-caption"><b>Table 2.</b>
    Functions and usage according to the distinction between SIEM and ESM.</div>
      <table >
        <thead  ><tr  ><th align='center' valign='middle' style='border-top:solid thin;border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Layer</th><th align='center' valign='middle' style='border-top:solid thin;border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >SIEM</th><th align='center' valign='middle' style='border-top:solid thin;border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >ESM</th></tr></thead><tbody  ><tr  ><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Main Function</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Centralized management of information and security events occurring within the organization.</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Centralized management of security information collected to monitor and operate security systems.</td></tr><tr  ><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Collection Save</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Collects information and logs on resources and security threats occurring within the organization (both structured and unstructured data).</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Collects security threat information required for security monitoring (structured data).</td></tr><tr  ><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Analysis Method</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Collects logs and events from security systems, server systems, networks, and applications, and analyzes them through security personnel.</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Consolidates security threat information from security systems and server systems, providing it to the security monitoring team.</td></tr><tr  ><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Analysis Results and Characteristics</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Correlation analysis of applications, users, and protocols. Applies security rules defined by security personnel. Detects new security threats such as APTs and ransomware.</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Detects network threats using rules such as IP/Port. Detects known attacks through short-term, large-scale analysis.</td></tr><tr  ><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Usability</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Integrates external security threat information and internal vulnerabilities for analysis. Used by security personnel to investigate security incidents (post-event security audit).</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Used for real-time security monitoring.</td></tr></tbody>
      </table>



</div>
<div class="html-table-wrap"
  id="applsci-14-11836-t003"
  
  data-position="float"
>
  <div class="html-table_wrap_td">
