<div class="html-table_show  mfp-hide " id="table_body_display_applsci-14-11836-t003">
  

      <div class="html-caption"><b>Table 3.</b>
    Information input structure for security incident targets, types, and input methods for customized corporate services.</div>
      <table >
        <thead  ><tr  ><th align='center' valign='middle' style='border-top:solid thin;border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Layer</th><th align='center' valign='middle' style='border-top:solid thin;border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Description</th></tr></thead><tbody  ><tr  ><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Security Incident Type Analysis</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Major Category: Internal, External <br> Subcategory: Hacking, Malware, Data Leakage, etc. <br> Minor Category: Email, Web, System, Network, Storage, Print, etc.</td></tr><tr  ><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Security Incident Target Protection</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Major Category: System, Network, Human, Process <br> Subcategory: PC, Server, IoT Devices, Smart Devices, Organization Chart, Access Control, etc.</td></tr><tr  ><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Security Incident Target Information Input</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Manual Input: IP range, system asset information, permission information, account information, organization chart, etc. <br> Automated Collection: Information collected via IP scans, etc.</td></tr></tbody>
      </table>



</div>
<div class="html-table-wrap"
  id="applsci-14-11836-t004"
  
  data-position="float"
>
  <div class="html-table_wrap_td">
    <div class="html-tablepopup html-tablepopup-link" data-counterslinkmanual = "https://www.mdpi.com/2076-3417/14/24/11836/display"
  href='#table_body_display_applsci-14-11836-t004'>
        <img data-lsrc="https://pub.mdpi-res.com/img/table.png" />
       <a class="html-expand html-tablepopup" data-counterslinkmanual = "https://www.mdpi.com/2076-3417/14/24/11836/display"
  href="#table_body_display_applsci-14-11836-t004"></a>
    </div>

  </div>
  <div class="html-table_wrap_discription">
    <b>Table 4.</b>
    Definition of internal and external security incident types.
  </div>
</div>
<div class="html-table_show  mfp-hide " id="table_body_display_applsci-14-11836-t004">
  

      <div class="html-caption"><b>Table 4.</b>
    Definition of internal and external security incident types.</div>
      <table >
        <thead  ><tr  ><th align='center' valign='middle' style='border-top:solid thin;border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Layer</th><th align='center' valign='middle' style='border-top:solid thin;border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Description</th></tr></thead><tbody  ><tr  ><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Operating System</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Data leakage due to missed security updates and antivirus program updates <br> Important file leakage due to poor management of shared folders <br> Leakage of important corporate data through P2P, messenger, etc. <br> System intrusion due to lack of access control service</td></tr><tr  ><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Web Service</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Personal information exposure due to database system vulnerabilities <br> Database access credentials leaked due to weak password settings <br> Personal information leakage caused by SQL injection attacks <br> Administrator privileges exposed due to poor configuration of web page access control <br> Rights exposed due to Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) vulnerabilities <br> System information leakage due to vulnerabilities in file transmission</td></tr><tr  ><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Network System</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Personal information and passwords leaked due to the lack of SSL encryption <br> Risk of direct network system attacks due to poor network configuration <br> Important corporate information leakage through wireless networks</td></tr></tbody>
      </table>



</div>
<div class="html-table-wrap"
  id="applsci-14-11836-t005"
  
  data-position="float"
>
  <div class="html-table_wrap_td">
    <div class="html-tablepopup html-tablepopup-link" data-counterslinkmanual = "https://www.mdpi.com/2076-3417/14/24/11836/display"
  href='#table_body_display_applsci-14-11836-t005'>
        <img data-lsrc="https://pub.mdpi-res.com/img/table.png" />
       <a class="html-expand html-tablepopup" data-counterslinkmanual = "https://www.mdpi.com/2076-3417/14/24/11836/display"
  href="#table_body_display_applsci-14-11836-t005"></a>
    </div>

  </div>
  <div class="html-table_wrap_discription">
    <b>Table 5.</b>
    Snort command.
  </div>
</div>
<div class="html-table_show  mfp-hide " id="table_body_display_applsci-14-11836-t005">
  

      <div class="html-caption"><b>Table 5.</b>
    Snort command.</div>
      <table >
        <thead  ><tr  ><th align='center' valign='middle' style='border-top:solid thin;border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Command</th><th align='center' valign='middle' style='border-top:solid thin;border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Description</th></tr></thead><tbody  ><tr  ><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >alert</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Rule action (Alert, Log, Pass, Drop, Reject, etc.)</td></tr><tr  ><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >tcp</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Protocol designation (Tcp, Udp, Icmp, Ip)</td></tr><tr  ><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >any</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Source IP (10.0.0.33)</td></tr><tr  ><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >any</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Source PORT (5001)</td></tr><tr  ><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >-&gt;</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Direction (-&gt;, &lt;&gt;): Indicates one-way and two-way directions, no reverse direction like “&lt;-”</td></tr><tr  ><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >msg</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >The message that will be alerted when the packet is detected</td></tr><tr  ><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >content</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >String to check in the packet payload(If checking binary values, expressed as “(00 01 02)” format)</td></tr><tr  ><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >nocase</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Case-insensitive detection</td></tr><tr  ><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Sid</td><td align='center' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-center' >Detection rule ID</td></tr></tbody>
      </table>



</div>
